# SECTION 5: KTU 2024 Scheme Examination Question Bank & Topic Recap

## 5.1 Part A Questions (3 Marks Each)

### Q1. [KTU University Exam – May 2024] 
**Explain how a DC motor's speed can be controlled using PWM. What is the role of the L293D driver IC?**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
- (1 mark) **PWM principle:** Speed is controlled by varying the **average voltage** delivered to the motor. The MOSFET/H-bridge switches fully ON/OFF at high frequency, varying the duty cycle D from 0 % to 100 %.
- (1 mark) **Average voltage equation:** $V_{avg} = D \times V_{supply}$. Higher D → higher average voltage → higher speed.
- (1 mark) **L293D role:** It is a **dual H-bridge driver** that provides bidirectional current control and high current drive (up to **600 mA per channel**, **1.2 A peak**) for the motor. The microcontroller pin cannot directly source/sink such current, so L293D acts as a **current amplifier and direction steerer**. EN pin receives the PWM signal for speed control, while IN1/IN2 select direction.

