### Q2. [KTU University Exam – Dec 2023]
**With the help of a 4-step excitation sequence, explain how a stepper motor can be rotated through 90° if the motor has 200 steps/revolution.**

**Model Answer (3 marks):**
- (1 mark) **Step angle:** $\theta_{step} = 360°/200 = 1.8°$ per full step.
- (1 mark) **Steps required for 90°:** $N = 90°/1.8° = 50$ full steps.
- (1 mark) **4-step sequence table (one phase ON):**

| Step | A | B | C | D |
|------|---|---|---|---|
| 1    | 1 | 0 | 0 | 0 |
| 2    | 0 | 1 | 0 | 0 |
| 3    | 0 | 0 | 1 | 0 |
| 4    | 0 | 0 | 0 | 1 |

- This sequence is applied repeatedly for 50 cycles to produce 90° rotation (CW or CCW depending on direction of sequence).

