#### Model Solution — (b) [7 marks]

**Circuit Description (2 marks):**
- LM35 Vcc → +5 V, GND → 0 V, Vout → ADC0804 V<sub>in</sub>+ (pin 6).
- ADC0804 V<sub>REF</sub>/2 (pin 9) decoupled with 0.01 µF → sets V<sub>REF</sub> = 5 V (full-scale).
- ADC0804 CLKR (pin 19) & CLKIN (pin 4) connected through **10 kΩ and 150 pF** giving $f_{CLK} \approx 606$ kHz (conversion time ≈ 110 µs).
- ADC0804 D0–D7 → 8051 P0.0–P0.7.
- ADC0804 WR (pin 3) → P3.1, RD (pin 2) → P3.0, INTR (pin 5) → P3.2 (INT0).

**Temperature Formula (1 mark):**
$$T(°C) = \frac{ADC \times 5.0}{2.56}$$

**C Program with UART (4 marks):**
```c
#include <reg51.h>

#define ADC_DATA P0
sbit ADC_WR   = P3^1;
sbit ADC_RD   = P3^0;
sbit ADC_INTR = P3^2;

void uart_init(void) {
    TMOD = 0x20;        // Timer1 Mode 2 (auto-reload)
    TH1  = 0xFD;        // 9600 baud @ 11.0592 MHz
    SCON = 0x50;        // Mode 1, 8-bit UART, REN enabled
    TR1  = 1;            // Start Timer1
}

void uart_tx(char c) {
    SBUF = c;
    while(TI == 0);
    TI = 0;
}

void uart_str(char *s) {
    while(*s) uart_tx(*s++);
}

void delay_ms(unsigned int ms) {
    unsigned int i, j;
    for(i = 0; i < ms; i++)
        for(j = 0; j < 1275; j++);
}

unsigned char read_adc(void) {
    unsigned char v;
    ADC_WR = 0; delay_ms(1); ADC_WR = 1;
    while(ADC_INTR == 1);
    ADC_RD = 0;
    v = ADC_DATA;
    ADC_RD = 1;
    return v;
}

void main(void) {
    unsigned char d;
    unsigned int temp;
    P0 = 0xFF;
    uart_init();
    uart_str("Temp Monitor Ready\r\n");
    while(1) {
        d = read_adc();
        temp = (d * 500) / 256;       // Integer °C
        uart_str("T = ");
        uart_tx((temp/10) + '0');
        uart_tx((temp%10) + '0');
        uart_str(" C\r\n");
        delay_ms(500);
    }
}
```

**Key formula used:** `temp = (adc * 500) / 256` — equivalent to `adc * 5 / 2.56`, scaled by 100 for integer math.

