#### Model Solution — (b) [7 marks]

**Step Calculations (2 marks):**
- $\theta_{step} = 1.8°$ (given).
- CW 180°: $N_{CW} = 180 / 1.8 = 100$ steps.
- CCW 90°: $N_{CCW} = 90 / 1.8 = 50$ steps.

**Excitation Sequence (1 mark):** 4-step, single-phase ON:

| Step | A | B | C | D |
|------|---|---|---|---|
| 1    | 1 | 0 | 0 | 0 |
| 2    | 0 | 1 | 0 | 0 |
| 3    | 0 | 0 | 1 | 0 |
| 4    | 0 | 0 | 0 | 1 |

**C Program (4 marks):**
```c
#include <reg51.h>

sbit A = P1^0;
sbit B = P1^1;
sbit C = P1^2;
sbit D = P1^3;

void delay_ms(unsigned int ms) {
    unsigned int i, j;
    for(i = 0; i < ms; i++)
        for(j = 0; j < 1275; j++);
}

void step_cw(void) {
    A=1; B=0; C=0; D=0; delay_ms(10);
    A=0; B=1; C=0; D=0; delay_ms(10);
    A=0; B=0; C=1; D=0; delay_ms(10);
    A=0; B=0; C=0; D=1; delay_ms(10);
}

void step_ccw(void) {
    A=0; B=0; C=0; D=1; delay_ms(10);
    A=0; B=0; C=1; D=0; delay_ms(10);
    A=0; B=1; C=0; D=0; delay_ms(10);
    A=1; B=0; C=0; D=0; delay_ms(10);
}

void main(void) {
    unsigned int i;
    while(1) {
        for(i = 0; i < 100; i++) step_cw();   // 180° CW
        delay_ms(500);
        for(i = 0; i < 50;  i++) step_ccw();  // 90° CCW
        A = B = C = D = 0;                    // De-energize: stop
        while(1);                              // Halt
    }
}
```

