## 5.3 KTU Examiner's Valuation Warning / Pitfall Callout

> [!WARNING]
> **Where students lose marks on this topic:**
> 1. **Forgetting to de-energize the stepper motor after the final step.** The motor continues to draw holding current and overheats. Always set coil lines to 0 after motion is complete.
> 2. **Not converting ADC value to integer correctly.** Floating-point division on 8051 is slow and often disabled in Keil default libraries. Use integer arithmetic: `temp = (adc * 500) / 256`.
> 3. **Confusing active-LOW and active-HIGH LED wiring.** The 8051 sinks more current than it sources, so active-LOW is the industry default. Mixing this up results in a non-functional board.
> 4. **Forgetting external pull-ups on Port 0.** Port 0 is open-drain; without 10 kΩ pull-ups, all reads from P0 return 0.
> 5. **Refresh rate too low for seven segment multiplex.** If you set $t_{ON} > 5$ ms per digit, the display flickers visibly. Examiners *will* deduct marks for flicker.
> 6. **PWM frequency outside motor's optimal band.** Below 20 Hz: audible whine. Above 25 kHz: switching losses dominate, torque drops.
> 7. **Wrong baud rate constant for 11.0592 MHz crystal.** TH1 = 0xFD for 9600 baud; using 0xFE or any other value corrupts UART data silently.

