## 5.4 Topic Recap & Important Things to Remember

- **All 8051 ports reset to 0xFF** (input-ready quasi-bidirectional). Write 1 to a port pin to make it input; write 0/1 to output.
- **Active-LOW is the standard** for 8051 LED and switch interfacing (sinks more current).
- **Mechanical switch debounce** requires **20 ms** software delay (between 5 ms and 30 ms is acceptable).
- **DC motor speed control** uses PWM with duty cycle D = t<sub>ON</sub> / T. L293D provides the H-bridge for bidirectional control.
- **PWM frequency for DC motor** should be **40 Hz – 25 kHz**. Common choice: **1 kHz** for smooth, silent operation.
- **Stepper motor step angle** = 360° / N, where N = steps per revolution. For 1.8° motor, N = 200.
- **4-step full-step sequence** energizes one coil at a time. **8-step half-step** alternates between one and two coils for finer resolution.
- **LM35 sensitivity is exactly 10 mV/°C**, linear, with 0 V output at 0 °C. Output range 0–1.5 V for 0–150 °C.
- **Temperature formula (8-bit ADC, 5 V ref):** T = (ADC × 5) / 2.56 °C.
- **Temperature formula (10-bit ADC, 3.3 V ref, LPC2148):** T = (ADC × 3.3) / 10.24 °C.
- **Seven segment Common-Cathode:** segment ON when bit = 1. **Common-Anode:** segment ON when bit = 0.
- **Multiplexed seven segment refresh** must exceed **60 Hz** to avoid flicker; use **2–5 ms per digit**.
- **8051 machine cycle** = 12 oscillator cycles. At 11.0592 MHz, machine cycle ≈ 1.085 µs.
- **Standard delay constant:** ≈ **1275 iterations of inner DJNZ loop = 1 ms** at 11.0592 MHz.
- **TMOD = 0x20, TH1 = 0xFD, SCON = 0x50** = 9600 baud UART at 11.0592 MHz.
- **ADC0804 requires a clock**; built with 10 kΩ + 150 pF on CLKR/CLKIN pins → ~606 kHz.
- **Port 0 of 8051 is open-drain** → always use external 10 kΩ pull-ups for HIGH output.

